{"word":"ἴχνος","slug":"ἴχνος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἴχνος</b></el> <el>(ἴχνος, εος,) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a track, footstep</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>a track, trace, clue</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <i>a foot</i> or <i>leg</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}